Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.redis.client

Interface BooleanResultHandler

  • public interface BooleanResultHandler
    Handler for Redis commands that return a boolean-like result.

    Redis uses integers for boolean results (0 = false, non-zero = true). This handler provides a more natural boolean interface.

    Commands with boolean results:

    • EXISTS - true if key exists
    • SETNX - true if key was set (didn't exist)
    • SISMEMBER - true if element is in set
    • EXPIRE - true if timeout was set
    • PERSIST - true if timeout was removed
    • HEXISTS - true if field exists in hash
    • MOVE - true if key was moved
    • RENAMENX - true if key was renamed
    Author:
    Chris Burdess
